Mkdirs grants you an ongoing, non-exclusive license to use the software components and templates included in the SaaS Starter Kit.

The license permits usage by a single individual, team, or organization (the Licensee) and does not transfer to additional individuals, teams, or organizations without explicit permission.

You can:

- Use Mkdirs to create unlimited end products.
- Modify Mkdirs components to create derivative works, subject to this license.
- Use Mkdirs to create projects for unlimited clients.
- Use Mkdirs to create end products sold to end users.
- Use Mkdirs to build and run SaaS applications where end users interact with your end product.

You cannot:

- Redistribute Mkdirs’s components or templates, even if modified, separately from an end product.
- Share your access to Mkdirs with anyone outside your team or organization without explicit permission.
- Use Mkdirs to create products that compete with Mkdirs or provide a SaaS starter kit in conflict with Mkdirs’s business.

Example Usage

Examples of permitted usage:

- Creating personal, team, or organizational websites or applications.
- Building commercial SaaS applications or web apps for clients.

Examples of prohibited usage:

- Creating a repository of Mkdirs (components) and sharing or selling it.
- Making a derivative product (e.g. starter kit) and offering it for sale or free.

Enforcement and Liability

Mkdirs reserves the right to revoke licenses in case of a material breach of this agreement. The liability of Mkdirs is limited to the refund of the license fee. This agreement is governed by the laws of Switzerland.

